---
import Base from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site, mailto } from '../config/site';
const schema={'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'ContactPage',name:'Contact INNO Transformer Temperature Controller Supplier'};
---
<Base title="Transformer Temperature Controller Supplier Contact | INNO" description="Contact INNO for OTI, WTI, BWY, BWR and transformer temperature monitoring system selection, current technical documents, supplier pricing and quotations." schema={schema}>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">Direct supplier contact</p><h1>Contact a Transformer Temperature Controller Supplier</h1><p>Email your transformer OTI, WTI, BWY, BWR or monitoring system requirement directly to INNO. This website does not use an inquiry form.</p><div class="actions"><a class="button" href={mailto('Transformer temperature controller supplier inquiry')}>Email {site.email}</a></div></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container grid two"><article class="prose"><h2>What to Include in a Transformer Temperature Inquiry</h2><ul class="email-checklist"><li>Transformer type, rating and application</li><li>Oil temperature indicator, winding temperature indicator or monitoring device</li><li>Existing full model and nameplate photo</li><li>Temperature range and required scale</li><li>Switch quantity, contact duty and purpose</li><li>Pt100, 4–20 mA or RS485 interface</li><li>Power supply and receiving equipment</li><li>Capillary length, bulb and mounting thread</li><li>Outline or installation drawing</li><li>Quantity, destination country and required date</li></ul><h3>Documents You Can Request</h3><p>Ask for the current model-specific datasheet, outline drawing, terminal diagram, applicable quality documents and commercial quotation.</p></article><article class="card"><h2>INNO Supplier Email</h2><p><a class="text-link" href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a></p><p>Attach specifications, drawings and photographs directly to the email. Clearly identify whether the measured value is top-oil temperature or simulated winding temperature.</p><a class="button" href={mailto('INNO OTI WTI BWY BWR quotation')}>Open email application</a></article></div></section>
</Base>
